#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:1
msgid "_validate_axis_limits"
msgstr "_validate_axis_limits"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:3
msgid "Firma"
msgstr "Signature"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:15
msgid "Che problema risolve"
msgstr "What problem it solves"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:17
msgid ""
"Converte e valida una coppia di limiti per assi o range, mantenendo messaggi di errore specifici "
"per il parametro che li ha richiesti."
msgstr ""
"Converts and validates a pair of axis or range limits while keeping error messages specific to "
"the parameter that requested them."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:19
msgid "Contratto sugli input"
msgstr "Input contract"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:21
msgid "`limits` deve essere una sequenza di esattamente due elementi."
msgstr "`limits` must be a sequence of exactly two elements."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:22
msgid "Stringhe e `bytes` vengono rifiutati esplicitamente."
msgstr "Strings and `bytes` are rejected explicitly."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:23
msgid "I due valori devono essere convertibili a `float` e finiti."
msgstr "Both values must be convertible to `float` and finite."

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:25
msgid "Dove viene usata"
msgstr "Where it is used"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:27
msgid "in [`histogram`](../../moduli/plot_utils/histogram.md) per `xlim`, `ylim` e `hist_range`"
msgstr "in [`histogram`](../../moduli/plot_utils/histogram.md) for `xlim`, `ylim`, and `hist_range`"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:28
msgid "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) per `xlim` e `ylim`"
msgstr "in [`lin_fit`](../../moduli/fit_utils/lin-fit.md) for `xlim` and `ylim`"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:30
msgid "Come fallisce"
msgstr "Failure modes"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:32
msgid "`ValueError` se `limits` non e una sequenza valida"
msgstr "`ValueError` if `limits` is not a valid sequence"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:33
msgid "`ValueError` se non contiene esattamente due elementi"
msgstr "`ValueError` if it does not contain exactly two elements"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:34
msgid "`ValueError` se contiene valori non finiti"
msgstr "`ValueError` if it contains non-finite values"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:36
msgid "Perche resta privata"
msgstr "Why it stays private"

#: ../../source/checks/plot_utils/validate-axis-limits.md:38
msgid ""
"E un validatore di supporto per la parte grafica. La sua utilita e interna, ma documentarla rende"
" piu leggibili le regole comuni di plotting."
msgstr ""
"It is a support validator for the plotting layer. Its usefulness is internal, but documenting it "
"makes the common plotting rules easier to read."

